74
00:04:00,118 --> 00:04:02,678
It retains sensory information for a very short period

75
00:04:02,698 --> 00:04:05,079
of time, such as a fraction of a second,

76
00:04:05,839 --> 00:04:07,660
without it being consciously processed.

77
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,020
For example, the persistence of vision

78
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:12,361
is due to sensory memory, and it allows us

79
00:04:12,441 --> 00:04:14,822
to perceive a 24 image per second display

80
00:04:15,322 --> 00:04:16,922
as an uninterrupted animation.

81
00:04:17,547 --> 00:04:19,868
It requires attention for the information

82
00:04:19,928 --> 00:04:24,009
to go to working memory, which is a short-term component

83
00:04:24,409 --> 00:04:26,970
that allows for temporary storage and manipulation

84
00:04:27,030 --> 00:04:30,450
of a very limited amount of new or already stored information.

85
00:04:31,031 --> 00:04:33,571
The system maintains active mental representation

86
00:04:33,851 --> 00:04:35,392
necessary to perform a task.

87
00:04:36,092 --> 00:04:38,713
The working memory requires heavy attentional resources

88
00:04:39,093 --> 00:04:40,533
and therefore is very limited.

89
00:04:41,013 --> 00:04:43,654
It is also easily disturbed, so please put your phones

90
00:04:43,914 --> 00:04:44,634
in silent mode.

91
00:04:46,423 --> 00:04:50,545
Long-term memory is a multiple system component

92
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:55,007
that allows us to store knowledge of events and facts,

93
00:04:55,347 --> 00:04:58,988
as well as skills, the know-how, and conditioned responses.

94
00:04:59,769 --> 00:05:02,650
The long-term memory has no known limits in space,

95
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:05,491
and it can potentially store information for a lifetime.

96
00:05:06,151 --> 00:05:08,572
