00:19:13,517 --> 00:19:16,678
So F2P game must mine the cognitive load

361
00:19:16,758 --> 00:19:17,438
in working memory.

362
00:19:19,671 --> 00:19:22,553
There are many ways to reduce the cognitive load here,

363
00:19:23,634 --> 00:19:25,435
such as distribute learning over time,

364
00:19:25,675 --> 00:19:26,516
which we're gonna see later.

365
00:19:27,056 --> 00:19:29,778
You can also use affordances to limit the cognitive load.

366
00:19:30,558 --> 00:19:32,540
What is intuitive does not need to be learned,

367
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:35,261
therefore requires less attentional resources to process.

368
00:19:35,822 --> 00:19:38,584
In design, an affordance gives or provides something

369
00:19:38,724 --> 00:19:40,385
that helps a user to do something.

370
00:19:41,345 --> 00:19:43,487
Now, four kinds of affordances in UX design.

371
00:19:44,067 --> 00:19:45,668
I'll give an example of each right after.

372
00:19:46,418 --> 00:19:47,678
You have physical affordance.

373
00:19:47,878 --> 00:19:49,298
That's a feature that helps users

374
00:19:49,318 --> 00:19:51,839
in doing a physical action in the interface.

375
00:19:52,259 --> 00:19:54,200
For example, a button that is large enough

376
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,360
so that users can click on it accurately.

377
00:19:57,620 --> 00:19:58,901
You have cognitive affordance.

378
00:19:59,201 --> 00:20:01,481
It enables thinking, learning, understanding,

379
00:20:01,681 --> 00:20:02,741
knowing about something.

380
00:20:02,902 --> 00:20:05,622
For example, a button label that helps user

381
00:20:06,182 --> 00:20:07,843
know what will happen if they click on it.

382
00:20:08,603 --> 00:20:10,843
Form follows function is a cognitive affordance.

383
00:20:11,913 --> 00:20:12,834
You have sensory affordance.

384
00:20:13,014 --> 00:20:15,515
It's a design feature that helps users sense something.

385
00:20:15,936 --> 00:20:17,597
For example, a label, font size,

386
00:20:17,657 --> 00:20:18,718
large enough to be discerned.

387
00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:20,959
And you have functional affordance.

388
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,902
It's a design feature that helps users accomplish a task.

389
00:20:24,302 --> 00:20:27,044
For example, a sort functionality in an inventory.

390
00:20:28,025 --> 00:20:29,666
There's a subtlety.

391
00:20:29,706 --> 00:20:33,048
The perceivable part of an affordance is a signifier.

392
00:20:33,889 --> 00:20:36,871
So as a designer, you care about placing signifiers

393
00:20:36,891 --> 00:20:39,293
to enable the players to perceive the affordances.

394
00:20:42,224 --> 00:20:46,528
So physical affordance facilitates physically doing something, such as a handle on a door

395
00:20:46,748 --> 00:20:48,831
physically helps you operating the door.

396
00:20:49,511 --> 00:20:53,816
So you want a button to be large enough to tap on it, to click on it, or you want two

397
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:56,779
buttons to not be too close to each other to avoid misclicks.

398
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,802
See the Fitts' Law for these things.

399
00:20:59,703 --> 00:21:02,726
Or on mobile, interactive areas to be comfortable to reach.

400
00:21:05,106 --> 00:21:10,991
A cognitive affordance, like we saw facilitates or enables thinking about something, they help users to know what to do.

401
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:16,476
So the pull handle offers both cognitive and physical affordance

402
00:21:16,856 --> 00:21:22,981
because it provides a physical means for pulling as well as a visual indication that pulling is the required action.

403
00:21:23,822 --> 00:21:29,607
In Fortnite, you have three different symbols representing three types of materials. Remember you can build and craft.

404
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:33,246
and how many of each the player has.

405
00:21:34,107 --> 00:21:36,853
So that helps players understand what they can do with it.

406
00:21:39,852 --> 00:21:41,593
Cognitive affordance can go wrong.

407
00:21:41,613 --> 00:21:43,314
This is called false affordance.

408
00:21:43,534 --> 00:21:45,376
It is when the perceived affordance is not

409
00:21:45,416 --> 00:21:47,277
the one intended, given the functionality.

410
00:21:48,538 --> 00:21:51,861
Here's the example of the axe in Fortnite.

411
00:21:53,162 --> 00:21:55,363
So you have a lot of weapons and tools.

412
00:21:55,744 --> 00:21:58,806
You actually have one tool that is really

413
00:21:58,926 --> 00:22:00,487
effective for harvesting, just one.

414
00:22:00,587 --> 00:22:01,288
It's the pickaxe.

415
00:22:01,868 --> 00:22:05,391
But you have all the other items you can have are melee weapons.

416
00:22:05,711 --> 00:22:07,032
So the axe is a melee weapon.

417
00:22:07,631 --> 00:22:13,055
Of course, originally it was not the design intention to put an axe in the player's hand

418
00:22:13,135 --> 00:22:15,697
and say, no, you cannot actually chop off trees with that.

419
00:22:16,778 --> 00:22:21,862
Initially they wanted to have one specific tool for each specific thing you can harvest,

420
00:22:21,942 --> 00:22:25,845
like the axe for the tree, the sledgehammer for a wall, and stuff like that.

421
00:22:25,985 --> 00:22:29,928
But it was too demanding, players didn't like that, it was not really fun, so they removed

422
00:22:29,948 --> 00:22:30,608
that functionality.

423
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:34,871
And there you end up with a false affordance because of that,

424
00:22:34,931 --> 00:22:36,532
because now players can have an axe,

425
00:22:37,313 --> 00:22:39,374
but it has to be used for meleeing

426
00:22:39,534 --> 00:22:41,375
and not for chopping trees.

427
00:22:43,217 --> 00:22:45,398
So false cognitive affordance misinform

428
00:22:45,418 --> 00:22:46,399
and mislead the players,

429
00:22:46,699 --> 00:22:48,140
and then it makes it much harder

430
00:22:48,580 --> 00:22:49,861
to teach them the right thing.

431
00:22:50,221 --> 00:22:51,902
And it's frustrating for the players on top of it.

432
00:22:52,443 --> 00:22:54,104
So you really have to pay attention to that.

433
00:22:54,284 --> 00:22:57,266
That's really the sort of things that happen just.

434
00:22:58,816 --> 00:23:00,998
It happens because the design changed,

435
00:23:01,378 --> 00:23:05,281
so you have to stay focused on that.

436
00:23:05,301 --> 00:23:06,823
Sensory affordance, easy one,

437
00:23:07,083 --> 00:23:08,584
helps players sense in something,

438
00:23:08,904 --> 00:23:10,285
seeing, hearing, feeling.

439
00:23:11,226 --> 00:23:12,687
This is what we call the perceptibility

440
00:23:12,727 --> 00:23:13,628
of sounds and feedback.

441
00:23:14,529 --> 00:23:16,551
It includes noticeability, discernibility,

442
00:23:16,651 --> 00:23:17,972
legibility in case of text,

443
00:23:18,372 --> 00:23:19,873
and audibility in case of sound.

444
00:23:21,054 --> 00:23:23,775
So in that case, of course that's a bug, it's not by design.

445
00:23:25,776 --> 00:23:33,920
When you die, you can click to respawn, but the text is hidden behind a health bar,

