so you don't have to do that again and again.

476
00:25:17,218 --> 00:25:19,519
So designers have to make sure, this is really useful,

477
00:25:19,859 --> 00:25:23,060
but you have to make sure that the functional affordance

478
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:25,881
you're designing is really gonna be useful to the player,

479
00:25:25,901 --> 00:25:28,541
and not just add noise or complexity.

480
00:25:29,342 --> 00:25:31,042
Refer you to the Pareto principle,

481
00:25:31,062 --> 00:25:33,603
it's like the 80-20 principle.

482
00:25:33,643 --> 00:25:37,224
80% of the time, people use only 20% of the functionalities.

483
00:25:37,624 --> 00:25:39,524
So be careful not to add too much stuff

484
00:25:39,564 --> 00:25:40,765
that peers are not gonna use.

485
00:25:43,226 --> 00:25:46,428
Some interfaces feel easy to use while others drive us nuts

486
00:25:46,608 --> 00:25:49,530
and requires manuals or sticky notes, in that example.

487
00:25:50,471 --> 00:25:52,332
It will greatly help remove barriers

488
00:25:52,412 --> 00:25:54,253
for your players' first steps in your game

489
00:25:55,154 --> 00:25:56,354
if you have good affordances,

490
00:25:56,715 --> 00:25:58,376
or should I say, good signifiers.

491
00:25:58,816 --> 00:26:01,758
Because if it doesn't, you'll need tutorial texts,

492
00:26:02,258 --> 00:26:04,159
or players will have to make an extra effort,

493
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:07,081
which they often don't, won't do it,

494
00:26:07,422 --> 00:26:11,244
to figure out on forums how to use a certain functionality.

495
00:26:14,188 --> 00:26:15,970
So the key takeaway here for discovery

496
00:26:17,190 --> 00:26:20,632
is you have to mind the attention limitations

497
00:26:20,752 --> 00:26:22,473
and the cognitive load for the player.

498
00:26:22,974 --> 00:26:24,835
Your main objective is to make sure

499
00:26:24,915 --> 00:26:26,976
that your game's gonna be easy to make sense of

500
00:26:27,797 --> 00:26:28,997
and to remove barriers.

501
00:26:30,058 --> 00:26:33,060
And this is by design, but if it's not by design,

502
